	It seems like a perfectly reasonable set of things to do and I'm surprised
	that more sites don't do it.  I think that this sort of thing should be either
	required or strongly suggested in the upcoming host requirements RFC.


David,

The HR RFC tries to confine itself strictly to software requirements as
opposed to configuration/operation requirements.  I believe that the
procedure you are recommending is a particular way an administrator
would configure the DNS, as opposed to the design and implementation of
the software; is this correct?  If so, it would not be appropriate to
include it in the HR RFC; it might belong in a revision of RFC-1033.

Bob Braden
Editor of HR RFC

